    "description": "The strategy seeks to monetize short term swing opportunities in large cap US technology equities by conditioning classic technical entry signals on a fractal and tail risk regime model. Daily data are used to compute multi horizon Hurst exponents, extreme return tail index, multifractal width, realized volatility and an implied over realized volatility ratio (from near at the money options), alongside RSI, Bollinger percent B, MACD, moving average trend, volume and VWAP deviation. These feature",
    "description_full": "The strategy seeks to monetize short term swing opportunities in large cap US technology equities by conditioning classic technical entry signals on a fractal and tail risk regime model. Daily data are used to compute multi horizon Hurst exponents, extreme return tail index, multifractal width, realized volatility and an implied over realized volatility ratio (from near at the money options), alongside RSI, Bollinger percent B, MACD, moving average trend, volume and VWAP deviation. These features classify each underlying into one of several regimes: trending up, trending down, mean reverting, elevated risk, or crisis. Signals are only acted on outside crisis regimes and are strongest when the detected regime aligns with either trend pullback and continuation setups or mean reversion setups, with signal strength scaled by fractal confidence and volatility mispricing proxies.",
